Lundblad
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,1599,1745]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<bibRefCitation author="Smit" box="[264,405,1599,1625]" pageId="5" pageNumber="23" refString="Smit, H. (2002) Two new water mite species from New Zealand (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Zootaxa, 61, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2002">
Smit (
<number box="[335,397,1599,1625]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
confirmed the conclusion of 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[751,900,1599,1625]" pageId="5" pageNumber="23" refString="Viets, K. O. (1978) Uber neue Wassermilben aus Australien (Acari, Hydrachnellae). Entomologica Scandinavica, 9, 265 - 278." type="journal article" year="1978">
Viets (
<number box="[827,890,1599,1625]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and lowered the ranking of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Flabellifrontipoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Flabellifrontipoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[627,759,1639,1664]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Frontipoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[627,759,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Frontipoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The subgenus has a Gondwanan distribution, with 
<number box="[325,354,1679,1705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="13.0">13</number>
taxa described from South 
<collectingCountry box="[687,788,1679,1705]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[806,942,1679,1705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1988) Water mites from Chile. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 42, 1 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">
Cook 
<number box="[880,942,1679,1705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), six taxa from 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1241,1679,1705]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Cook 
<number box="[264,324,1719,1745]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1986.0">1986</number>
) and nine taxa from 
<collectingCountry box="[568,725,1719,1745]" name="New Zealand" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[740,876,1719,1745]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1983) Rheophilic and hyporheic water mites of New Zealand. Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="1983">
Cook 
<number box="[813,876,1719,1745]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
